In this article, President Biden shares his thoughts on Rosalynn Carter, the former First Lady. He mentions that he was on the phone with the family when she was put in hospice and praises the Carter family for bringing grace to the office. President Biden also highlights Jimmy Carter's post-presidency work, describing him as an incredible person who helped others without seeking financial gain. He emphasizes the integrity of both Jimmy and Rosalynn Carter and mentions that he was the first person to endorse Jimmy Carter when he ran for U.S. senator. President Biden concludes by expressing his hope that the family is satisfied and happy that they were able to be together.